{"name": "sci-soft-models", "metadata": {"name": "sci-soft-models", "version": "0.3.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Natural Language :: English", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT License", "documentation_url": "https://evamaxfield.github.io/sci-soft-models", "dependencies": ["dataclasses-json", "requests", "torch", "transformers"], "summary": "Computational Models for Understanding Scientific Software", "upload_time": 1733272246}, "documentation": ["# Scientific Software (Predictive) Models\n\nComputational predictive models to assist in the identification, classification, and study of scientific software.\n\n## Models\n\n### Developer-Author Entity Matching\n\nThis model is a binary classifier that predicts whether a developer and an author are the same person. It is trained on a dataset of 3000 developer-author pairs that have been annotated as either matching or not matching.\n\n#### Usage\n\nGiven a set of developers and authors, we use the model on each possible pair of developer and author to predict whether they are the same person. The model returns a list of only the found matches in `MatchedDevAuthor` objects, each containing the developer, author, and the confidence of the prediction.\n\n```python\nfrom sci_soft_models import dev_author_em\n\ndevs = [\n    dev_author_em.DeveloperDetails(\n        username=\"evamaxfield\",\n        name=\"Eva Maxfield Brown\",\n    ),\n    dev_author_em.DeveloperDetails(\n        username=\"nniiicc\",\n    ),\n]\n\nauthors = [\n    \"Eva Brown\",\n    \"Nicholas Weber\",\n]\n\nmatches = dev_author_em.match_devs_and_authors(devs=devs, authors=authors)\nprint(matches)\n# [\n#   MatchedDevAuthor(\n#       dev=DeveloperDetails(\n#           username='evamaxfield',\n#           name='Eva Maxfield Brown',\n#           email=None,\n#       ),\n#       author='Eva Brown',\n#       confidence=0.9851127862930298\n#   )\n# ]\n```\n\n<h2>Extra Notes</h2>\n<details>\n\n### Developer-Author-EM Dataset\n\nThis model was originally created and managed as a part of [rs-graph](https://github.com/evamaxfield/rs-graph) and as such, to regenerate the dataset for annotation, the following steps can be taken:\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/evamaxfield/rs-graph.git\ncd rs-graph\ngit checkout c1d8ec89\npip install -e .\nrs-graph-modeling create-developer-author-em-dataset-for-annotation\n```\n\n[Link to annotation set creation function](https://github.com/evamaxfield/rs-graph/blob/c1d8ec8999a7a26e5d1669e9531adaad13245393/rs_graph/bin/modeling.py#L168).\n\n</details>\n"], "modules": [{"name": "sci_soft_models.tests.test_dev_author_em", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [{"name": "sci_soft_models.tests.test_dev_author_em.test_dev_author_em_matching_authors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Test the matching of authors and developers."]}, {"name": "sci_soft_models.tests.test_dev_author_em.test_dev_author_em_partial_devs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Test the matching of authors and developers with partial devs."]}, {"name": "sci_soft_models.tests.test_dev_author_em.test_dev_author_em_no_matching_authors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Test the matching of authors and developers with no matches."]}], "variables": [{"name": "sci_soft_models.tests.test_dev_author_em.EXAMPLE_DEVS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "sci_soft_models.tests.test_dev_author_em.EXAMPLE_PARTIAL_DEVS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "sci_soft_models.tests.test_dev_author_em.EXAMPLE_MATCHING_AUTHORS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "sci_soft_models.tests.test_dev_author_em.EXAMPLE_NO_MATCHING_AUTHORS", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "sci_soft_models.dev_author_em.main", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [{"name": "sci_soft_models.dev_author_em.main.get_model_details", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "ModelDetails", "xref": {"fqname": "sci_soft_models.dev_author_em.types.ModelDetails", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Get the name and version of the model.\n\nReturns\n-------\nModelDetails\n    The name and version of the model.", "##############################################################################"]}, {"name": "sci_soft_models.dev_author_em.main.load_dev_author_em_model", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "use_available_device", "type": {"name": "bool | str", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "Pipeline", "xref": {"fqname": "transformers.Pipeline", "project": "transformers"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Load the author-dev EM model.\n\nParameters\n----------\nuse_available_device: bool | str | int\n    Whether to use the available device, by default True\n    Can pass a string for a specific device to use.\n\nReturns\n-------\nPipeline\n    The author-dev EM model."]}, {"name": "sci_soft_models.dev_author_em.main.match_devs_and_authors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "devs", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "DeveloperDetails", "xref": {"fqname": "sci_soft_models.dev_author_em.main.DeveloperDetails", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "authors", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"